00:17:52,895 --> 00:17:55,067
Who's Jules?
- That's me.

267
00:17:55,068 --> 00:17:58,498
Can we talk?
- Don't harass him.

268
00:17:58,499 --> 00:17:59,817
"Justice," your word.

269
00:18:00,077 --> 00:18:02,570
Let's talk about harassment, Professor-?

270
00:18:02,571 --> 00:18:03,749
Murat.

271
00:18:03,906 --> 00:18:04,938
Come.

272
00:18:05,831 --> 00:18:08,409
Come on; I'm not gonna eat you.

273
00:18:09,261 --> 00:18:12,026
You're wrong, she was just
a friend.

274
00:18:12,093 --> 00:18:14,156
Yeah?
- Yeah.

275
00:18:14,398 --> 00:18:17,695
What do you want?
- Her phone.

276
00:18:17,696 --> 00:18:19,992
It's not here.
- No?

277
00:18:19,993 --> 00:18:22,006
Welcome to my home.

278
00:18:25,485 --> 00:18:26,730
That's it.

279
00:18:27,107 --> 00:18:29,622
And not her phone?
- No...

280
00:18:29,982 --> 00:18:32,536
Your desk?
- Yes.

281
00:18:32,990 --> 00:18:36,302
Well then!

282
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:39,239
There you both are.

283
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,660
And a boyfriend?

284
00:18:40,674 --> 00:18:43,916
Where were you last night?
- In bed, ask my roommates.

285
00:18:44,197 --> 00:18:47,095
If we go out, we write it down.

286
00:18:48,048 --> 00:18:49,368
The rules!

287
00:18:50,345 --> 00:18:53,423
I know, I would sneak out too.

288
00:18:54,838 --> 00:18:57,978
How come your girlfriend left
Murat's class?

289
00:18:57,979 --> 00:19:00,333
She said nothing to me.
- <i>Diony.</i>

290
00:19:00,888 --> 00:19:03,569
She hadn't spoken to you

291
00:19:03,570 --> 00:19:06,241
about Murat: your good master,
your "precious"?

292
00:19:06,242 --> 00:19:09,101
Our "guru"? You all say that.

293
00:19:09,102 --> 00:19:10,215
Is that so?

294
00:19:11,315 --> 00:19:13,205
And who says that?

295
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:16,189
He treats us all like adults.

296
00:19:16,331 --> 00:19:18,292
You aren't yet.

297
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,706
Well done! 4 for her first schedule.

298
00:19:36,707 --> 00:19:39,144
Why did she change major? What
happened between you?

299
00:19:39,145 --> 00:19:41,330
Stop your innuendo.

300
00:19:41,331 --> 00:19:43,660
You're too close to them!

301
00:19:44,824 --> 00:19:46,621
I killed her, is that what you think?

302
00:19:46,622 --> 00:19:48,471
And what I did-

303
00:19:48,472 --> 00:19:50,646
Whoa! Four hours of detention I'm

304
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:52,252
I'm giving you, let me watch.
- Good morning.

305
00:19:52,253 --> 00:19:54,190
Phil Bernadet, a professor.

306
00:19:54,565 --> 00:19:56,471
Mr. Murat is paranoid, yeah?

307
00:19:56,472 --> 00:19:59,639
Well, paranoids often have
good reason to be.

308
00:20:00,941 --> 00:20:04,371
Did Claire's departure surprise you?

309
00:20:04,372 --> 00:20:07,765
I said nothing.
- Where are you going?

310
00:20:07,766 --> 00:20:09,596
A class, it seems.

311
00:20:11,056 --> 00:20:12,361
Hold hold hold;

312
00:20:12,362 --> 00:20:16,056
I'm working too, even if you
can't see it.

313
00:20:16,525 --> 00:20:19,994
Listen, Claire was a passionate,
endearing student

314
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,954
who was brilliant but unpredictable.

315
00:20:22,993 --> 00:20:28,110
Unpredictable doesn't rhyme
with "controlled."

316
00:20:28,674 --> 00:20:30,885
So you know my nickname, "the guru."

317
00:20:30,886 --> 00:20:34,969
The origin of "guru" is "guide,"
a teacher.

318
00:20:34,970 --> 00:20:38,803
A good teacher is the one who
knows nothing precisely.

319
00:20:38,841 --> 00:20:42,132
Where were you last night between
10 pm and midnight?

320
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,671
At mine.

321
00:20:44,147 --> 00:20:45,631
Is there a witness?

322
00:20:45,828 --> 00:20:47,640
No.
- That's stupid.

323
00:20:48,224 --> 00:20:49,427
That's how it is!

324
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:51,366
Yes, but it's stupid.
- You asked.

325
00:21:25,694 --> 00:21:26,835
Maude? It's me.

326
00:21:26,836 --> 00:21:29,969
I'm coming home.
<i>- Tell me frankly:</i>

327
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:33,955
did you ever suspect Murat of
inappropriate behavior?

328
00:21:34,206 --> 00:21:37,050
Never.
- Who's speaking, the stepmother

329
00:21:37,534 --> 00:21:40,362
or the principal protecting her
school's reputation?

330
00:21:40,363 --> 00:21:42,089
<i>Your wife.</i>

331
00:21:59,357 --> 00:22:00,709
How's your investigation?

332
00:22:00,981 --> 00:22:04,028
I'm not idle, with 492 students.

333
00:22:04,029 --> 00:22:05,512
Talk to Rufus.

334
00:22:05,513 --> 00:22:08,311
Rufus? The nutcase?
- He threatened

335
00:22:08,312 --> 00:22:11,451
a friend with a knife.
- Yeah? Why?

336
00:22:11,452 --> 00:22:13,689
We were crossing his land,
it's a shortcut.

337
00:22:13,792 --> 00:22:16,620
Yeah; that's not stupid.

338
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:18,557
Thanks for the tip, honey!

339
00:22:20,166 --> 00:22:21,963
NO TO THE AGRICULTURE

340
00:22:21,964 --> 00:22:23,939
SCHOOL EXPANSION

341
00:22:34,445 --> 00:22:37,179
ACTION

342
00:22:37,798 --> 00:22:41,067
"Elections, not words."
He's not wrong.

343
00:22:41,637 --> 00:22:42,933
SOLIDARITY LIBERTY The
ECOLOGY REVOLUTION revolutionary!

344
00:22:42,934 --> 00:22:44,378
MILITIA EVERYWHERE The
JUSTICE NOWHERE revolutionary!

345
00:22:44,379 --> 00:22:46,278
With his big barracks!

346
00:22:46,636 --> 00:22:50,152
Sol-i-dar-i-ty with
pen-si-o-ners!

347
00:22:50,605 --> 00:22:53,136
"Militia everywhere, justice nowhere!"

348
00:22:53,855 --> 00:22:55,549
All the "autographs."

349
00:22:55,995 --> 00:22:57,113
Anybody there?

350
00:23:03,980 --> 00:23:05,273
Ho!

351
00:23:06,495 --> 00:23:07,698
Anyone?

352
00:23:07,987 --> 00:23:09,182
Whoa!

353
00:23:09,183 --> 00:23:12,729
What do you want?
- Hey-I'm the heat!

354
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:15,845
I didn't see.
- Thanks for the welcome?

355
00:23:18,350 --> 00:23:21,281
Is it OK you bomb people, like
a wingless plane?

356
00:23:21,282 --> 00:23:23,829
I was kidding.

357
00:23:24,206 --> 00:23:26,624
High fashion humor?

358
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:28,948
And the knife kids say you had,
that was for laughs too?

359
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:30,693
Well, it wasn't funny.

360
00:23:30,694 --> 00:23:35,215
But they hit me on the noggin with
their two-wheelers.

361
00:23:35,216 --> 00:23:37,350
I wouldn't have hurt them.

362
00:23:38,403 --> 00:23:41,060
Coffee?
- I wouldn't mind one.

363
00:23:41,913 --> 00:23:44,405
And better than at "the
warden's", huh?

364
00:23:44,624 --> 00:23:47,439
Is she the one who ratted me out?

365
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,033
Pfft, not even.

366
00:23:49,408 --> 00:23:52,705
Look: not the biggest.
- Not the smallest.

367
00:23:52,706 --> 00:23:54,971
Put yourself in my place.
- Show me.

368
00:23:57,315 --> 00:23:59,088
You don't like the school.

369
00:23:59,089 --> 00:24:04,451
It's been 15 years since they built it

370
00:24:04,452 --> 00:24:05,694
on unbuildable land.

371
00:24:05,695 --> 00:24:06,834
What a crock!

372
00:24:07,088 --> 00:24:09,166
It's not common, believe it
if you want,

373
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:10,612
if you know what I mean.

374
00:24:10,613 --> 00:24:12,604
I wanted to ask if you know her,

375
00:24:12,605 --> 00:24:16,307
the little one: "Rosa Luxembourg."

376
00:24:16,308 --> 00:24:17,385
Yes? No?

377
00:24:17,386 --> 00:24:19,949
You're here because you were
told about a knife?

378
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:22,489
No, for the wolf in the sheep fold

379
00:24:22,490 --> 00:24:25,323
who killed this sheep, this morning.

380
00:24:25,324 --> 00:24:27,632
Never seen her in my life.

381
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:29,268
Yeah? Swear?
- Swear.

382
00:24:29,269 --> 00:24:30,542
You're sure?

383
00:24:30,543 --> 00:24:33,142
The fantasy:

384
00:24:33,143 --> 00:24:37,268
Rufus the sociopath, the marginalized.

385
00:24:37,269 --> 00:24:40,346
The psychopath. It's real life.

386
00:24:40,442 --> 00:24:43,020
"There is never anything left of
the lived experience."

387
00:24:43,021 --> 00:24:45,481
"Some grain will oxidize its paraffin."

388
00:24:45,482 --> 00:24:46,864
Yes, Castel. What's the matter?

389
00:24:46,865 --> 00:24:50,832
The young girl and Murat weren't
just teacher and student.

390
00:24:51,028 --> 00:24:52,747
Listen to what she sent him:

391
00:24:52,748 --> 00:24:54,536
<i>We think alike.</i>

392
00:24:54,594 --> 00:24:57,126
<i>But you started earlier.</i>

393
00:24:57,167 --> 00:24:58,854
<i>And it's as if</i>

394
00:24:59,493 --> 00:25:01,430
<i>you waited for me.</i>
- Fuck.

395
00:25:05,584 --> 00:25:06,764
What are you doing?

396
00:25:06,895 --> 00:25:07,973
Come on!

397
00:25:08,213 --> 00:25:09,632
Yeah yeah yeah.
- Let go of me!

398
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:10,922
Leave him alone!

399
00:25:10,923 --> 00:25:12,184
It's fine!

400
00:25:12,526 --> 00:25:14,034
Don't worry!

401
00:25:15,901 --> 00:25:17,471
You have to calm down!

402
00:25:18,384 --> 00:25:19,556
So...

403
00:25:19,932 --> 00:25:21,776
Kids!

404
00:25:25,144 --> 00:25:27,348
<i>And it's as if</i>

405
00:25:27,673 --> 00:25:29,275
<i>you had waited for me.</i>

406
00:25:31,713 --> 00:25:33,010
<i>You're right.</i>

407
00:25:33,137 --> 00:25:36,840
<i>Everything will change. Those able
to adapt will survive.</i>

408
00:25:37,939 --> 00:25:39,337
<i>Nothing will last.</i>

409
00:25:39,338 --> 00:25:42,619
<i>Let's live the present together.</i>

410
00:25:42,620 --> 00:25:45,373
I saw those videos.

411
00:25:47,066 --> 00:25:48,550
<i>I'm not afraid of the night,</i>

412
00:25:48,551 --> 00:25:50,469
<i>of the sun.</i>

413
00:25:50,553 --> 00:25:54,498
<i>I'm not afraid of your body that
envelops me to disappear.</i>

414
00:25:55,024 --> 00:25:57,087
<i>I'm afraid of myself-</i>
- Goodbye!

415
00:25:58,019 --> 00:26:02,113
It's a personality cult. A real Stalin!

416
00:26:02,153 --> 00:26:08,107
It wasn't for me.
- Yes? Why didn't you tell me?

417
00:26:08,269 --> 00:26:12,629
Out of respect for Claire, to preserve
her privacy.

418
00:26:12,630 --> 00:26:18,682
Like Stalin, Mao:
protector of youth.

419
00:26:18,897 --> 00:26:22,600
And why did this young girl skip
your classes?

420
00:26:22,728 --> 00:26:25,370
I wanted to explain to her

421
00:26:25,371 --> 00:26:28,378
she was confusing love and
admiration.

422
00:26:28,424 --> 00:26:29,690
Poor kid,

423
00:26:29,808 --> 00:26:31,968
she declared her feelings and got
a punch in the nose.

424
00:26:31,988 --> 00:26:33,796
It must have been awkward.

425
00:26:33,939 --> 00:26:38,744
She was mortified, she felt belittled.

426
00:26:38,745 --> 00:26:45,001
You might have stopped
the thing from the outset.

427
00:26:45,079 --> 00:26:47,430
I should have.
- "I should have."

428
00:26:47,729 --> 00:26:49,292
Yes, but it's so easy

429
00:26:49,293 --> 00:26:53,745
to impress a teen when you're
her father's age.

430
00:26:53,746 --> 00:26:56,024
and take advantage
of the kid maybe.

431
00:26:56,025 --> 00:26:58,231
No way, I never took "advantage."

432
00:26:58,232 --> 00:27:00,057
Never?

433
00:27:00,348 --> 00:27:04,208
A teacher-student relationship is
never equal to equal.

434
00:27:04,446 --> 00:27:06,954
The adult has authority.

435
00:27:06,962 --> 00:27:10,119
It was up to you to quickly say Stop.

436
00:27:10,126 --> 00:27:13,149
I chose to ignore her messages.

437
00:27:14,002 --> 00:27:15,892
So that she would get tired of it.

438
00:27:16,418 --> 00:27:17,566
That's it.

439
00:27:18,548 --> 00:27:22,838
You wanted to play Nabokov by
Lolita-ing the kid.

440
00:27:23,523 --> 00:27:26,789
And then make a date that goes wrong.
- No.

441
00:27:26,854 --> 00:27:27,788
No?
- No!

442
00:27:27,808 --> 00:27:30,781
You wouldn't be the first.
- Good. anyway-

443
00:27:32,256 --> 00:27:35,678
for the lie by omission we'll put
0 out of 20. OK?

444
00:27:35,825 --> 00:27:38,284
Get me my stuff.
- Stuff...

445
00:27:38,285 --> 00:27:44,705
Yeah, we're going to sample your DNA
and compare it with hers.

446
00:27:45,008 --> 00:27:46,704
<i>Voila.</i> Thank you so much.

447
00:27:46,705 --> 00:27:49,633
Mouth open-MOUTH OPEN!

448
00:27:51,363 --> 00:27:53,746
Close your eyes, it will slide in better.

449
00:27:53,747 --> 00:27:54,840
There!

450
00:27:56,382 --> 00:27:59,513
No, not in there, it's too small.

451
00:28:00,062 --> 00:28:02,040
He'll fit. Go on!

452
00:28:03,735 --> 00:28:05,305
Watch your hands!

453
00:28:08,141 --> 00:28:11,492
It won't do to lash out at my colleague.

454
00:28:11,493 --> 00:28:13,585
It's nothing to do with him.

455
00:28:13,759 --> 00:28:15,517
Hey, give me that scarf.

456
00:28:15,951 --> 00:28:17,646
We're not playing Hangman.

457
00:28:17,906 --> 00:28:19,875
And forget the coffee.

458
00:28:19,876 --> 00:28:21,289
Put that away.

459
00:28:23,649 --> 00:28:25,071
A complete map...

460
00:28:30,911 --> 00:28:32,677
We need to trace the guy.

461
00:28:32,921 --> 00:28:35,530
I've received the geolocation data
on her phone.

462
00:28:35,531 --> 00:28:39,482
So?
- No connection with Murat.

463
00:28:40,452 --> 00:28:44,455
You're a pessimist, you know that?

464
00:28:45,022 --> 00:28:46,593
No? Me neither.

465
00:28:56,585 --> 00:29:00,979
This is the last sector where her
phone pinged.

466
00:29:02,286 --> 00:29:04,474
Let's go around the corner.
- Yes.

467
00:29:04,497 --> 00:29:08,809
Question the locals. Considering
everything, it will go quickly.

468
00:29:08,810 --> 00:29:12,294
I'll come back for you.
- Where are you going?

469
00:29:12,295 --> 00:29:13,871
You do your sector,

470
00:29:13,872 --> 00:29:15,833
I'll do the penultimate one where
she last texted.

471
00:29:15,834 --> 00:29:17,287
Thank you, nice.

472
00:29:17,288 --> 00:29:20,544
Walking will do you good.
- Sure.

473
00:29:21,114 --> 00:29:22,793
Going... and: bye.

474
00:29:55,561 --> 00:29:57,607
Sir! Gendarmerie.

475
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,803
What are you doing here?

476
00:30:03,053 --> 00:30:04,333
I live there.

477
00:30:04,334 --> 00:30:05,895
In there?
- Yes.

478
00:30:06,201 --> 00:30:08,990
Teacher salaries have gone down?

479
00:30:09,733 --> 00:30:11,608
Good smell!

480
00:30:12,038 --> 00:30:13,226
It's compost.

481
00:30:15,928 --> 00:30:18,326
Corpse compost, does that
work too?

482
00:30:19,763 --> 00:30:23,607
In the USA they're going to
legalize it.

483
00:30:24,076 --> 00:30:27,545
Big business, huh?

484
00:30:28,083 --> 00:30:30,130
I'm here because

485
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:36,294
my colleagues tell me Claire's phone
pinged around here yesterday.

486
00:30:36,349 --> 00:30:37,903
Yes, I saw her.

487
00:30:38,654 --> 00:30:41,850
That's why. What did she want?

488
00:30:42,693 --> 00:30:45,912
Well, advice.
- About?

489
00:30:46,115 --> 00:30:50,264
She changed major and had
fallen behind.

490
00:30:51,326 --> 00:30:53,662
She wanted to talk to me about it.
- Yes, I understand.

491
00:30:54,317 --> 00:30:55,609
I understand.

492
00:30:56,201 --> 00:30:59,053
So, suddenly: bang!

493
00:31:00,521 --> 00:31:04,193
You went into this RV to discuss

494
00:31:05,038 --> 00:31:06,538
something special with her?

495
00:31:06,646 --> 00:31:08,537
Are you kidding?

496
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:11,583
I only know the students in
my class.

497
00:31:11,662 --> 00:31:14,639
Yeah, why I'm looking for you.

498
00:31:15,326 --> 00:31:19,287
Well then; what happened?

499
00:31:20,419 --> 00:31:24,303
Nothing. She didn't insist, and left.

500
00:31:24,304 --> 00:31:25,658
She left...

501
00:31:27,752 --> 00:31:28,955
Who are you calling?

502
00:31:28,956 --> 00:31:30,025
A colleague.

503
00:31:30,056 --> 00:31:32,181
To search down to your skin.

504
00:31:32,354 --> 00:31:33,800
Yeah, it's me!

505
00:31:33,889 --> 00:31:36,421
We're going to do a search.

506
00:31:36,725 --> 00:31:40,756
It's an RV. Bring 2 or 3 people.

507
00:31:40,780 --> 00:31:43,397
Yeah. No, the man is scared.

508
00:31:43,398 --> 00:31:46,187
You're the last to have seen her,

509
00:31:46,188 --> 00:31:47,789
we have to.

510
00:31:48,472 --> 00:31:49,660
Go on, ciao.

511
00:31:50,105 --> 00:31:51,175
Coffee?

512
00:32:04,003 --> 00:32:05,972
Here you are!

513
00:32:05,973 --> 00:32:09,066
Sorry, Captain.
- It's over there. Chop-chop!

514
00:32:09,067 --> 00:32:11,466
A call. Who's calling me?

515
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:12,987
Eh?

516
00:32:13,036 --> 00:32:15,232
Well? A date, Oscar?

517
00:32:15,233 --> 00:32:20,515
Glass dust and a shard in
her left arch.

518
00:32:20,516 --> 00:32:24,263
She may have fallen on broken glass.

519
00:32:24,264 --> 00:32:28,945
It remains to be seen if it's
glass for food...

520
00:32:28,946 --> 00:32:31,216
Elementary, my dear Oscar.

521
00:32:31,318 --> 00:32:33,912
...or glass from a building.

522
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:35,955
Thanks, honey. Ciao.

523
00:32:38,472 --> 00:32:39,764
What?

524
00:32:41,517 --> 00:32:43,767
Prepared to lose?
- And you?

525
00:32:43,768 --> 00:32:45,993
Ha, that's my business.

526
00:32:45,994 --> 00:32:47,454
I'm a teacher.

527
