00:48:28,452 --> 00:48:31,092
What gendarme?
- Come here.

791
00:48:31,771 --> 00:48:33,740
Come see something.

792
00:48:38,466 --> 00:48:39,779
I said nothing.

793
00:48:40,017 --> 00:48:43,363
I hope so, for I'd be sad if something
happened

794
00:48:43,364 --> 00:48:46,056
and your dad went back to jail

795
00:48:46,057 --> 00:48:47,691
for his aggression.

796
00:48:48,065 --> 00:48:49,995
I learned some stuff about him
on the Net.

797
00:49:09,073 --> 00:49:11,237
I can do this.
- No, it's fine.

798
00:49:26,386 --> 00:49:27,761
It's so beautiful.

799
00:49:29,963 --> 00:49:32,096
What is it, dear?
- I'm sorry.

800
00:49:33,020 --> 00:49:35,458
What is it?
- How could I not see it?

801
00:49:36,370 --> 00:49:40,169
It was evident there was a risk of abuse.

802
00:49:43,728 --> 00:49:45,049
What happened between them?

803
00:49:45,050 --> 00:49:46,573
What are you talking about?

804
00:49:46,574 --> 00:49:47,589
With Murat.

805
00:49:48,064 --> 00:49:49,720
Nothing, surely.

806
00:50:17,567 --> 00:50:19,981
She preferred acting to complaining.

807
00:50:19,982 --> 00:50:21,528
We must honor her memory, OK?

808
00:50:24,845 --> 00:50:26,502
Jules.
- Let go of me!

809
00:50:26,503 --> 00:50:29,643
Wait; when exactly does this end?
- Drop it.

810
00:50:30,354 --> 00:50:32,956
You know things-
- And you?

811
00:50:37,067 --> 00:50:38,271
Mr. Murat!

812
00:50:40,512 --> 00:50:42,715
A teacher is not a friend
or brother.

813
00:50:43,559 --> 00:50:46,832
It's not clear what you are
to kids,

814
00:50:46,833 --> 00:50:48,771
and you didn't help my
daughter's life.

815
00:50:49,051 --> 00:50:50,754
I'll go, Mr. Duret.
- What happened at

816
00:50:50,755 --> 00:50:53,636
your last school? They fired
you, right?

817
00:50:54,115 --> 00:50:57,787
No, I decided to leave.
- Then why are you here?

818
00:50:58,614 --> 00:50:59,914
Get out!

819
00:51:00,294 --> 00:51:01,747
I SAID, GET OUT!

820
00:51:11,087 --> 00:51:12,364
Aiee!

821
00:51:17,444 --> 00:51:18,705
Achoo!

822
00:51:18,749 --> 00:51:19,976
Working overtime?

823
00:51:19,977 --> 00:51:21,522
I'm learning the trade.

824
00:51:23,024 --> 00:51:24,438
What do you want now?

825
00:51:25,637 --> 00:51:27,309
According to your coworkers' statements

826
00:51:27,310 --> 00:51:30,372
you left here at around 2200 hours.

827
00:51:31,609 --> 00:51:34,195
Where were you? Smoke break?
- Yeah.

828
00:51:34,488 --> 00:51:36,340
Did you smoke the whole pack?

829
00:51:36,526 --> 00:51:39,409
Because you were gone

830
00:51:39,652 --> 00:51:42,774
more than 30 minutes.
- OK, I went to the Duret's.

831
00:51:43,134 --> 00:51:45,064
<i>voila!</i>

832
00:51:45,931 --> 00:51:47,384
I'm understanding better.

833
00:51:47,932 --> 00:51:51,292
Did you go to fix their window?

834
00:51:51,970 --> 00:51:54,939
To bury the hatchet.
- Well, Pocahontas;

835
00:51:55,595 --> 00:51:57,220
why didn't you tell me?

836
00:51:58,214 --> 00:52:00,448
There was no one home.

837
00:52:00,464 --> 00:52:02,940
Or she didn't come to the door.

838
00:52:02,987 --> 00:52:04,456
No. She wasn't there.

839
00:52:05,167 --> 00:52:06,307
We're closing.

840
00:52:08,206 --> 00:52:09,249
Well-

841
00:52:09,868 --> 00:52:12,525
What a welcome, thanks!
Are you freaking out?

842
00:52:12,526 --> 00:52:14,982
Or is it my colleague who's scary?

843
00:52:14,983 --> 00:52:17,118
No one scares me, okay?

844
00:52:19,274 --> 00:52:22,110
Let's get off to a good start.
All right?

845
00:52:23,616 --> 00:52:26,070
Claire was your best friend,

846
00:52:26,071 --> 00:52:28,984
she must've told you
about Mr. Murat.

847
00:52:28,985 --> 00:52:29,993
No, never.

848
00:52:33,086 --> 00:52:35,586
What did you think of the "guru"?

849
00:52:37,102 --> 00:52:38,876
He wasn't my teacher.

850
00:52:39,945 --> 00:52:41,679
And as a guy?

851
00:52:43,047 --> 00:52:46,508
He checked me out sometimes.
- He threatened you?

852
00:52:46,641 --> 00:52:48,258
Threatened? Why?

853
00:52:48,711 --> 00:52:50,741
It was flattering.

854
00:52:51,617 --> 00:52:53,414
It's a network of gerontophiles!

855
00:53:35,474 --> 00:53:37,752
SLAUGHTERHOUSES

856
00:53:58,712 --> 00:54:01,204
Jules? Calm down.

857
00:54:01,877 --> 00:54:03,901
Don't move, I'm coming!

858
00:54:22,547 --> 00:54:25,052
What did you do?
- I screwed up.

859
00:54:25,758 --> 00:54:27,110
I could have succeeded.

860
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:30,454
Succeed at what?

861
00:54:30,820 --> 00:54:33,422
Claire wanted to take the
slaughterhouse director hostage.

862
00:54:33,423 --> 00:54:35,563
To expose the cruelty.

863
00:54:37,530 --> 00:54:40,475
It hurts, I need treatment.

864
00:54:40,476 --> 00:54:42,101
Foolish!

865
00:54:57,353 --> 00:55:00,702
"The teacher at the slaughterhouse."
Was that the message?

866
00:55:00,703 --> 00:55:02,103
Thanks, you can go.

867
00:55:02,697 --> 00:55:04,548
What were you doing there?

868
00:55:05,376 --> 00:55:08,494
I suspected Jules was preparing
something.

869
00:55:09,447 --> 00:55:12,509
What are you doing to them? To their heads?

870
00:55:12,510 --> 00:55:14,392
One dead, one injured.

871
00:55:14,393 --> 00:55:16,257
It's easy to blame me.

872
00:55:16,875 --> 00:55:19,758
What about the parents?
- All right!

873
00:55:19,759 --> 00:55:21,940
Two students per class will
suffer incest,

874
00:55:21,941 --> 00:55:25,220
but abandoning a kid by the
highway is rare.

875
00:55:25,221 --> 00:55:26,957
You, I mean.

876
00:55:26,997 --> 00:55:31,293
Wasn't the hostage-taking your idea?

877
00:55:31,294 --> 00:55:32,756
Certainly not.

878
00:55:33,139 --> 00:55:35,006
It was Claire's idea.

879
00:55:35,255 --> 00:55:37,565
Mental. In short, always wrong.

880
00:55:37,566 --> 00:55:40,167
What other bad ideas did she have?

881
00:55:40,764 --> 00:55:42,561
I don't know.
- Think.

882
00:55:43,015 --> 00:55:44,913
Well... the boar.

883
00:55:44,914 --> 00:55:47,335
The one at the vet?

884
00:55:47,608 --> 00:55:51,491
Claire wanted to hide it
so it wouldn't be shot.

885
00:55:52,225 --> 00:55:55,233
Deborah calmed her down.
- Poor animal.

886
00:55:55,781 --> 00:55:56,906
The pig.

887
00:55:58,006 --> 00:56:00,483
Good. Take the bracelets
off him, please.

888
00:56:05,153 --> 00:56:08,387
The investigating judge will summon
you on the break-in.

889
00:56:08,709 --> 00:56:10,100
Be careful, I'm watching you.

890
00:56:10,404 --> 00:56:12,841
Not like you watch teens.

891
00:56:12,842 --> 00:56:16,178
Don't say that.
- Everyone says it.

892
00:56:17,044 --> 00:56:20,896
Look, of course I notice certain
situations around me...

893
00:56:21,834 --> 00:56:23,014
One thinks about things.

894
00:56:23,272 --> 00:56:25,795
...high school students.
- Even better!

895
00:56:26,123 --> 00:56:29,981
But because of what they give off,

896
00:56:29,982 --> 00:56:33,356
something that sets them apart in
the eyes, their attitude,

897
00:56:33,357 --> 00:56:37,021
or character... but not how
you mean it.

898
00:56:37,545 --> 00:56:40,451
You mean if I had you for a teacher,

899
00:56:40,452 --> 00:56:43,187
I wouldn't have failed?
- You failed?

900
00:57:04,768 --> 00:57:08,377
Where are they?
- The board has fired you.

901
00:57:09,674 --> 00:57:12,620
But without proof?
- The break-in at the slaughterhouse,

902
00:57:12,621 --> 00:57:16,086
dangerous statements.
- I hoped you'd support me.

903
00:57:16,087 --> 00:57:19,255
I did. There's too much.

904
00:57:29,052 --> 00:57:32,732
Bernardet! Don't pretend you
don't see me.

905
00:57:34,421 --> 00:57:38,186
You wouldn't have written to the board
to force me out?

906
00:57:39,166 --> 00:57:41,652
I could have but it's not worth it.

907
00:57:42,087 --> 00:57:43,532
You did it to yourself.

908
00:57:50,691 --> 00:57:53,636
EMERGENCY

909
00:57:58,821 --> 00:57:59,954
Hey, Julot!

910
00:58:00,629 --> 00:58:01,872
The gendarme.

911
00:58:02,690 --> 00:58:05,875
My son won't say anything.
- Our son.

912
00:58:05,876 --> 00:58:08,316
Not without a lawyer.
- Why?

913
00:58:08,317 --> 00:58:11,289
Mr. Murat is responsible for the
slaughterhouse,

914
00:58:11,290 --> 00:58:13,733
he manipulated my son.
- Our son.

915
00:58:13,734 --> 00:58:17,780
Family solidarity? That's right,
of course!

916
00:58:17,823 --> 00:58:21,065
You want a lawyer and a scapegoat.

917
00:58:21,101 --> 00:58:25,586
I want the girl's murderer. Do you
want more corpses?

918
00:58:25,587 --> 00:58:26,605
Of course not.

919
00:58:26,606 --> 00:58:27,765
"Of course not."

920
00:58:27,766 --> 00:58:30,731
You want to be called to the morgue?
- No more.

921
00:58:30,732 --> 00:58:34,078
"No more"? So come with me.
- Fuck.

922
00:58:34,240 --> 00:58:36,591
What's with the "fuck"?
Stop being rude.

923
00:58:37,232 --> 00:58:39,450
You need a physiotherapist.

924
00:58:39,924 --> 00:58:43,166
Good god, they shouldn't be allowed
to talk to you like that.

925
00:58:43,167 --> 00:58:44,248
In.

926
00:58:45,600 --> 00:58:47,710
Why bring me back here?

927
00:58:47,881 --> 00:58:50,217
My parents are waiting for me.

928
00:58:50,631 --> 00:58:53,272
To succeed, you have to abort
your parents.

929
00:58:53,417 --> 00:58:55,542
Let that sink in, OK?

930
00:58:55,994 --> 00:58:57,728
Little question:

931
00:58:57,896 --> 00:59:00,644
the slaughterhouse raid, who
thought of it?

932
00:59:00,645 --> 00:59:01,885
You or Claire?

933
00:59:02,573 --> 00:59:03,753
Claire.

934
00:59:04,137 --> 00:59:05,755
It was like her hobby.

935
00:59:06,643 --> 00:59:08,260
And your hobby, was it her?

936
00:59:08,774 --> 00:59:11,259
No, she wasn't my girl.

937
00:59:12,188 --> 00:59:14,118
You wanted her to be both
girl and friend.

938
00:59:14,468 --> 00:59:16,531
She refused, you killed her.

939
00:59:16,779 --> 00:59:18,232
Not at all.

940
00:59:19,136 --> 00:59:20,386
I didn't kill her.

941
00:59:21,346 --> 00:59:25,846
I'm wondering something: why didn't
she choose you?

942
00:59:26,238 --> 00:59:28,335
Do you know who she liked best?
- No.

943
00:59:28,336 --> 00:59:29,348
You don't know?
- No.

944
00:59:29,349 --> 00:59:31,203
Who?
- No.

945
00:59:31,223 --> 00:59:32,285
Who...

946
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:35,013
No!

947
00:59:35,639 --> 00:59:38,100
Not him?
- No, not him.

948
00:59:39,136 --> 00:59:41,409
Good, listen to something for
two minutes.

949
00:59:47,206 --> 00:59:49,266
You don't want to be
an informer, fine.

950
00:59:49,267 --> 00:59:50,983
But I will go with my
favorite theory.

951
00:59:50,999 --> 00:59:54,818
Jail is for him or for you, choose.

952
00:59:57,269 --> 00:59:58,382
Murat.

953
00:59:58,402 --> 01:00:00,925
I saw him with Claire the night
she died.

954
01:00:00,926 --> 01:00:02,193
That's it.

955
01:00:02,585 --> 01:00:06,242
You gave in fast, you wouldn't have
made a good Resistance fighter.

956
01:00:07,176 --> 01:00:08,285
Golly.

957
01:00:13,840 --> 01:00:15,051
Are you resigning?

958
01:00:15,650 --> 01:00:18,220
They're forcing me, I'll respond.

959
01:00:19,595 --> 01:00:22,486
Resisting is really good.

960
01:00:23,622 --> 01:00:25,763
I can go?
- Yes.

961
01:00:25,764 --> 01:00:29,208
You forgot something.
- What?

962
01:00:29,209 --> 01:00:33,111
In front of your door, it's dirty,
you have to sweep.

963
01:00:33,306 --> 01:00:35,485
I didn't do anything.

964
01:00:36,860 --> 01:00:41,618
Yet you didn't tell me you saw
Claire the night of the murder:

965
01:00:41,619 --> 01:00:43,689
lie by omission.

966
01:00:44,160 --> 01:00:46,824
It's a lot, no?

967
01:00:50,099 --> 01:00:52,997
Hey! Wait for me.

968
01:00:55,460 --> 01:00:58,272
I jostled a gendarme.

969
01:00:58,375 --> 01:01:01,180
Are you stopping me?
- Don't tempt me.

970
01:01:01,478 --> 01:01:04,095
Who told you I saw Claire?

971
01:01:04,096 --> 01:01:08,741
Someone who told me it
was happening.

972
01:01:09,063 --> 01:01:10,305
Wow!

973
01:01:11,057 --> 01:01:12,565
It's nice,

974
01:01:12,743 --> 01:01:16,599
a little secret date.
- Jules told you!

975
01:01:17,649 --> 01:01:20,889
He was jealous, suspicious, so
he followed me.

976
01:01:23,162 --> 01:01:26,437
I wanted to see her to convince her

977
01:01:26,438 --> 01:01:29,156
to come back to class, but she avoided me.

978
01:01:29,157 --> 01:01:32,319
She never visited?
- Until that day.

979
01:01:32,320 --> 01:01:34,965
<i>Are you following us?
- No, I was walking around.</i>

980
01:01:34,966 --> 01:01:37,825
She was about to crack.

981
01:01:37,826 --> 01:01:41,856
I made a 7 pm appointment to talk
with her.

982
01:01:41,857 --> 01:01:46,205
OK; 7pm, time of the crime.

983
01:01:46,532 --> 01:01:47,939
So what happened?

984
01:02:00,336 --> 01:02:03,710
Claire was in a hurry to be elsewhere.

985
01:02:04,178 --> 01:02:05,569
And as she was leaving...

986
01:02:06,929 --> 01:02:08,578
What?
- She kissed me,

987
01:02:10,196 --> 01:02:12,141
like a goodbye kiss.

988
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:21,235
Castel, at 7 pm Claire was with Murat.
Does that sound weird to you?

989
01:02:21,243 --> 01:02:24,267
Someone said-what was it?

990
01:02:24,268 --> 01:02:27,077
Not possible. At 7pm her phone was
in the middle of the countryside.

991
01:02:27,078 --> 01:02:29,107
So someone stole it.

992
01:02:39,161 --> 01:02:40,371
All right, love?
- Yeah.

993
01:02:47,278 --> 01:02:49,451
Say, about the Claire thing:

994
01:02:49,452 --> 01:02:50,856
after coming here,

995
01:02:50,857 --> 01:02:52,418
why didn't she have her phone?

996
01:02:53,700 --> 01:02:55,184
I don't know,

997
01:02:55,575 --> 01:02:57,614
she dropped it?

998
01:02:57,615 --> 01:02:59,391
Of course.
- Hello.

999
01:03:01,325 --> 01:03:03,028
That doesn't bother you,
does it?

1000
01:03:03,481 --> 01:03:06,074
Why so nervous during the search?
That's why you pay me!

1001
01:03:06,075 --> 01:03:08,669
You've no reason to get all defensive.

1002
01:03:08,670 --> 01:03:10,458
Move, you can explain it to me.

1003
01:03:10,903 --> 01:03:13,192
Don't bother, no one's going to
steal your stuff.

1004
01:03:14,506 --> 01:03:15,662
So long, love.
- Bye.

1005
01:03:16,277 --> 01:03:17,439
Yeah.

1006
01:03:17,459 --> 01:03:19,778
No handcuffs?
- If you want.

1007
01:03:20,942 --> 01:03:23,271
You think you're in an American movie.

1008
01:03:23,661 --> 01:03:25,645
Here, do it yourself.

1009
01:03:37,388 --> 01:03:38,779
Handcuffs!

1010
01:04:00,904 --> 01:04:02,795
Is he going to last a long time?

1011
01:04:03,576 --> 01:04:04,525
What?

1012
01:04:08,655 --> 01:04:10,068
I didn't kill her.

1013
01:04:10,107 --> 01:04:13,092
So much the better, one less suspect.

1014
01:04:13,271 --> 01:04:15,068
Let's say someone else killed her:

1015
01:04:15,069 --> 01:04:17,139
before she died, what'd you do?

1016
01:04:17,163 --> 01:04:18,616
I took her mobile.

1017
01:04:18,617 --> 01:04:21,147
Why, for the plan?
- What?

1018
01:04:21,171 --> 01:04:22,515
For her plan?

1019
01:04:22,940 --> 01:04:23,983
No...

1020
01:04:24,003 --> 01:04:26,425
When she changed majors,

1021
01:04:26,686 --> 01:04:30,530
I thought it had something to
do with Yannick.

1022
01:04:30,531 --> 01:04:32,830
Something distasteful?

1023
01:04:35,487 --> 01:04:39,886
At the end of a class, she forgot
her mobile.

1024
01:04:40,667 --> 01:04:43,152
You stole it?

1025
01:04:43,987 --> 01:04:48,557
No, I stopped-I looked at
the files on it.

1026
01:04:49,527 --> 01:04:53,166
You're not "juleferryien."
- What?

1027
01:04:53,968 --> 01:04:56,828
She knew it was me, I was the
last one in the room.

1028
01:04:56,829 --> 01:04:58,920
So that's why she went to see you,

1029
01:04:58,937 --> 01:04:59,939
She wanted to snitch on you,

1030
01:04:59,940 --> 01:05:02,311
and you killed her.
- No.

1031
01:05:02,312 --> 01:05:04,444
I got rid of it.

1032
01:05:04,445 --> 01:05:07,529
The body?
- The phone! Shit!

1033
01:05:07,530 --> 01:05:11,328
Hey, no big words.

1034
01:05:11,329 --> 01:05:13,305
Wipe your nose.

1035
01:05:14,863 --> 01:05:19,356
There's where you abandoned me.
- See, I came back.

1036
01:05:19,503 --> 01:05:20,644
There's the pond.

1037
01:05:20,739 --> 01:05:22,887
The pond? It's about time.

1038
01:05:23,778 --> 01:05:27,332
So; one, two;

1039
01:05:28,301 --> 01:05:29,504
well...

1040
01:05:30,730 --> 01:05:32,105
Shall I go?
- Yes.

1041
01:05:32,106 --> 01:05:34,091
Pay attention!

1042
01:05:43,882 --> 01:05:46,413
Isn't that a bit far?
- No.

1043
01:05:46,975 --> 01:05:50,615
I have colleagues you will stay
like that for hours.

1044
01:05:51,035 --> 01:05:52,620
There, I found it.

1045
01:05:52,621 --> 01:05:54,558
See, I was telling the truth.

1046
01:05:54,559 --> 01:05:57,030
The truth is you obstructed the
investigation,

1047
01:05:57,031 --> 01:05:58,972
that won't cut it.

1048
01:05:59,159 --> 01:06:03,261
Help me, I'm not gonna do
