01:22:53,957 --> 01:22:55,137
Hee hee!

1302
01:22:55,138 --> 01:22:57,644
Gendarmerie! Let us pass.

1303
01:22:57,727 --> 01:23:01,671
You didn't mention that he threatened
a student with a knife.

1304
01:23:02,335 --> 01:23:05,812
We were counting on you in
the investigation.

1305
01:23:05,813 --> 01:23:08,326
What was he doing at your place the
night of the murder?

1306
01:23:08,327 --> 01:23:09,608
He wasn't.

1307
01:23:09,609 --> 01:23:11,527
He wasn't there.

1308
01:23:11,709 --> 01:23:17,130
Maybe Rufus stole the jewelry
while she was out;

1309
01:23:17,131 --> 01:23:19,214
Her stepdaughter surprised him-

1310
01:23:19,215 --> 01:23:20,932
He killed her.
- That works.

1311
01:23:20,933 --> 01:23:25,158
And when the lady realizes Rufus
is the killer,

1312
01:23:25,159 --> 01:23:27,766
she says nothing and covers for him,

1313
01:23:27,767 --> 01:23:30,417
for old time's sake-you follow me?

1314
01:23:30,498 --> 01:23:35,006
Or out of guilt, for dumping him.
- That's it;

1315
01:23:35,263 --> 01:23:36,481
that's it, right?

1316
01:23:37,600 --> 01:23:38,779
No answer.

1317
01:23:39,060 --> 01:23:42,395
No problem: we'll take the DNA
from his van.

1318
01:23:42,726 --> 01:23:46,016
We'll find evidence Claire was in it,
alive or dead.

1319
01:23:46,328 --> 01:23:48,821
By the way, where did he kill her,
the woods?

1320
01:23:48,822 --> 01:23:50,126
It's not him.

1321
01:23:50,659 --> 01:23:51,972
"It's not him"!

1322
01:23:52,798 --> 01:23:55,025
It's not him; well shit then.

1323
01:23:55,338 --> 01:23:57,073
If by chance it's not him:

1324
01:23:57,104 --> 01:24:01,354
in fairy tales, heteronormative sexist
ones of course,

1325
01:24:02,127 --> 01:24:05,900
if the killer isn't Prince Charming, it's?

1326
01:24:05,904 --> 01:24:08,475
The stepmother.
- And that works.

1327
01:24:23,792 --> 01:24:25,386
I returned earlier than expected.

1328
01:24:27,457 --> 01:24:29,566
A broken window, something
had happened.

1329
01:24:31,502 --> 01:24:33,916
I remembered the threats
against Claire.

1330
01:24:41,065 --> 01:24:43,344
The power was out.

1331
01:24:46,538 --> 01:24:48,382
Someone had entered.

1332
01:25:34,327 --> 01:25:35,577
<i>Claire?</i>

1333
01:25:56,072 --> 01:25:57,372
<i>*Hello?*</i>

1334
01:25:57,899 --> 01:26:00,188
<i>I knew you would call me back.</i>

1335
01:26:00,797 --> 01:26:02,407
<i>It's over for me.</i>

1336
01:26:03,197 --> 01:26:04,361
<i>*What?*</i>

1337
01:26:05,039 --> 01:26:07,180
<i>I killed her.
- *Who?*</i>

1338
01:26:07,490 --> 01:26:09,271
<i>Antoine's daughter.</i>

1339
01:26:11,378 --> 01:26:12,503
<i>*I'm coming.*</i>

1340
01:26:19,431 --> 01:26:21,657
The daughter of my love.

1341
01:26:21,793 --> 01:26:24,475
It's not your fault, you didn't
do it on purpose.

1342
01:26:24,476 --> 01:26:26,764
You didn't know it was her.

1343
01:26:26,765 --> 01:26:28,178
What does it change?

1344
01:26:28,378 --> 01:26:31,089
Antoine knew it was tense between
her and me.

1345
01:26:31,090 --> 01:26:35,129
That's why you called Rufus?
- He told me to keep quiet.

1346
01:26:36,051 --> 01:26:38,801
He told me to keep quiet, it was an
accident and I couldn't bring Claire back.

1347
01:26:40,279 --> 01:26:42,662
A principal who kills a student;

1348
01:26:45,041 --> 01:26:47,150
I let myself be led.

1349
01:26:47,151 --> 01:26:51,154
It's his fault. He cleans everything up,
tells you to stay quiet,

1350
01:26:51,155 --> 01:26:54,929
