burglary, by breaking the window.

1357
01:27:15,021 --> 01:27:17,498
But she had glass shards on her face.

1358
01:27:17,499 --> 01:27:21,220
I would have given her the damn
bracelet. But I lied.

1359
01:27:21,548 --> 01:27:23,955
A pig with a lawyer would be a surprise.

1360
01:27:24,173 --> 01:27:26,619
She didn't need money,

1361
01:27:26,620 --> 01:27:30,064
she needed attention and listening.

1362
01:27:30,197 --> 01:27:31,541
Right?
- Right.

1363
01:27:31,542 --> 01:27:32,643
Right.

1364
01:27:41,408 --> 01:27:44,392
Your wife wanted to denounce herself.

1365
01:27:45,088 --> 01:27:46,838
But she turned to Rufus.

1366
01:27:49,164 --> 01:27:52,929
To say nothing and not go down
for Claire.

1367
01:27:55,646 --> 01:28:00,036
It's my fault, I should have understood
my daughter better.

1368
01:28:00,705 --> 01:28:05,315
A little means a lot in life, remember
the happy parts.

1369
01:28:07,908 --> 01:28:09,208
Captain?

1370
01:28:09,744 --> 01:28:11,236
How is this?

1371
01:28:14,062 --> 01:28:18,633
"Her age escaped childhood, laughing
like innocence."

1372
01:28:18,680 --> 01:28:21,141
Where's this from?
- An 18th century poem,

1373
01:28:21,263 --> 01:28:24,201
for her headstone next to
her mother's.

1374
01:28:26,606 --> 01:28:27,906
It's nice.

1375
